5:
Thank you for coming here today. I
apologize for the wait.
8:
Pay it no mind. Considering you
asked for Giselle, I assume there has
been a development in her case?
11:
Perhaps. Could I ask you to take a
look at this?
19:
Proceed with caution. Even a finger
prick will cause the pierced flesh to
rot away.
24:
Is this a cryptic artifact? 
That's quite the power...
29:
It is, and an illegal one at that. It
seems the adventurer who had it
bought it from someone on the
black market.
34:
Wait... Could that seller be related to
the accusations against Giselle?
38:
It's likely. Do you have any
recollections of this item or this
sketch of the seller based on the
adventurer's testimony?
44:
No, I don't recognize this person... or
this arrow.
47:
I see... I had thought there was a
possibility you'd know them... It
seems I've wasted your time.
51:
If I may... What will happen to that
arrow?
55:
The Arcane Academy's inspection
has deemed it a highly dangerous
item, so it will likely be sealed away.
59:
I see... Could I take one more look at
it?
62: Just be careful not to hurt yourself.
66:
Hmm... This looks familiar... But why...
Ah.
70:
I believe I have an idea. Could I ask
you to accompany me somewhere?
75:
This area should meet the
conditions you specified. The land
here is devoid of nutrients. Not even
grass grows here.
87:
And with that, all we have to do now
is wait.
90: So how long do we wait? A few days?
93: No, I recommend a full year.
102:
I believe this arrow holds the power
to revitalize elemental activity.
104:
When it pierces a living creature,
that activity is overstimulated,
causing the body to break down.
107:
However, if it is used on desolate
soil, it should act as a fertilizer of
sorts.
111:
Whoa, that's amazing. How did you
know?
115:
I've never seen this artifact before,
but I have seen something similar. 
It was about the size of a nail and
used for potted plants.
117:
So I believe we can expect these
lands to become more bountiful in
the coming year.
121:
A weapon in one person's hand may
be a tool in another's... I think you
just proved that.
124:
It's true that many cryptic artifacts
are considered cursed due to their
dangerous powers, but that's not all
there is to them.
126:
That's why I always try to picture the
potential within each piece I find...
130:
What kind of person created this
object? For what purpose? Just
thinking about it gets my heart
racing! Why, I'd—
134:
Ah, apologies. I was beginning to
ramble, wasn't I?
139:
Please don't apologize. I'd love to
hear more.
142:
Is that so? Well, I have plenty more
we can talk about.
147:
I shall report this matter to the
academy. And Giselle...
150:
Would you be willing to help us out
with other cryptic artifact
inspections?
154:
Your wits and knowledge of these
items would prove very useful to our
operations.
156: ...That is, if you are willing, of course.
159:
Hehe, I would love to accept your
proposal.
161:
But are you sure? Wouldn't bringing
someone like me in cause issues?
164:
My colleagues and I understand
that sometimes rules are meant to
be broken.
166:
As long as you file your paperwork, 
it should be fine.
170:
But I already finished reporting all
my artifacts...
174:
It appears we will be requesting
further documents. You can't pull
one over on us, Giselle.
180:
Oh dear... This paperwork is turning
out to be a bigger hassle than the
accusations against me...
